Time Value of Money: A dollar today is worth more than a dollar in the future due to the potential earning capacity.
This concept is crucial in evaluating long-term projects.
Capital Budgeting: This process involves evaluating long-term investments and projects,
considering the time value of money to determine their worth.
Interest Rate Example: Using an interest rate of 10%, the video illustrates how the present
value of a long-term investment (like a machine producing $1 per year for a billion years)
is calculated to be significantly lower than its total future value.
